      "publisher": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "Lux Jewels"},
      "inLanguage": "en-CA",
      "breadcrumb": {
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
          {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://engagementringincanada.com/"},
          {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Learn", "item": "https://engagementringincanada.com/learn/"},
          {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Moissanite vs Lab-Grown Diamond", "item": "https://engagementringincanada.com/learn/moissanite-vs-lab-grown-diamond/"}
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {"@type": "Question", "name": "Will moissanite pass a diamond tester?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Many will on older thermal testers. Moissanite is thermally conductive similarly to diamond. Newer multi-tester tools using electrical conductivity can distinguish them. A trained gemologist can identify moissanite by its double refraction and distinctive fire pattern."}},
        {"@type": "Question", "name": "Does moissanite look fake or cheap?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Moissanite is a beautiful gemstone. In indirect lighting it's difficult to distinguish from diamond. In strong direct light, higher fire (coloured flashes) is the main visible difference. Whether this looks 'better' or 'different' is a personal preference."}},
        {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is the main visual difference between moissanite and lab-grown diamond?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Moissanite has higher dispersion (0.104 vs 0.044 for diamond), producing more coloured light flashes (fire). In strong direct light or sunlight, moissanite shows more rainbow-like sparkle than diamond. In indirect light, the difference is subtle."}},
        {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much cheaper is moissanite than lab-grown diamond?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Moissanite is typically 50-70% less expensive than lab-grown diamond at equivalent visible sizes. A 6.5mm colourless moissanite (1.0ct diameter equivalent) is approximately C$400-C$800 in Canada vs C$1,400-C$2,200 for a 1.0ct G/VS2 Excellent lab-grown diamond."}}
